.NET Framework 3.5.name: SDK_BaseSystem
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: The Base System SDK script provides a bridge to core system SDK methods.
.NET Framework 3.5.remarks: This is an abstract class to implement the interface required by all implemented SDKs.

methods.name: ForceInterleavedReprojectionOn(bool force)
methods.summary: The ForceInterleavedReprojectionOn method determines whether Interleaved Reprojection should be forced on or off.

params.value: If true then Interleaved Reprojection will be forced on, if false it will not be forced on.

methods.name: IsDisplayOnDesktop()
methods.summary: The IsDisplayOnDesktop method returns true if the display is extending the desktop.
methods.returns: Returns true if the display is extending the desktop

methods.name: ShouldAppRenderWithLowResources()
methods.summary: The ShouldAppRenderWithLowResources method is used to determine if the Unity app should use low resource mode. Typically true when the dashboard is showing.
methods.returns: Returns true if the Unity app should render with low resources.
